column1: #Text=The Miami Heat defeated the Indiana Pacers , 113 - 95 , at American Airlines Arena on Saturday evening .
#Text=The Heat were expected to win this game easily and they took care of business in this wire - to - wire win .
#Text=In fact , the Heat led for the entirety of the second half , as they outscored the Pacers , 30 - 16 , in the third quarter .

column1: #Text=The assist - to - turnover ratio was the decisive statistic , with Miami recording 23 assists to 16 turnovers , while Indiana committed 15 turnovers to just 16 assists .
#Text=The Pacers ( 30 - 29 ) have now won five of their last six games , as they continue to falter .

column1: #Text=Jeff Teague was second on the team , finishing with 16 points , three rebounds and six assists .
#Text=Thaddeus Young was the only other starter in double figures , as he totaled 13 points , five rebounds and four assists .

column1: #Text=On deck for Indiana is a home matchup against the Atlanta Hawks on Friday .
#Text=The Heat ( 27 - 32 ) have now won four of their last six games , as they continue to falter .
#Text=Goran Dragic was the player of the game , as he accumulated 21 points , two rebounds and four assists on 8 - of - 12 shooting .
#Text=Hassan Whiteside recorded a double - double , totaling 22 points and 17 rebounds .
#Text=Dion Waiters was the only other starter in double figures , accruing 22 points , two rebounds and three assists .
#Text=Miami will look to play better on Thursday in a home matchup against the Toronto Raptors .

column6: Miami played well and won this game
